1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. Nc3 Bg7 4. e4 d6 5. Nf3 O-O 6. Be2 e5 7. O-O Nc6 8. d5
Ne7 9. b4 Nh5 10. g3 f5 11. Nd2 Nf6 12. c5 f4 13. Nc4 g5 14. Ba3 Bh3 15. Re1
Rf7 16. b5 Nc8 17. Bb2 Re7 18. c6 b6 19. a4 Qe8 20. a5 Rb8 21. axb6 axb6 22.
Ra3 h5 23. Qd3 Qg6
{ (A thematic Pawn Cascade, which grabs space, places pressure against d6, and allows White to open the c-file by cxd6 if he feels it’s advantageous to do so) (Preparing his own space gaining Pawn Cascade by …g5-g4) [Diagram] }
24. Rea1 Re8 25. Ra8 Rxa8 26. Rxa8 Rf8 27. Nd2 Bh6 28. Bf1 Bxf1 29. Nxf1 g4 30.
gxf4 exf4 31. Qc4 g3 32. hxg3 fxg3 33. fxg3 h4 34. e5 Be3+ 35. Nxe3 $2 Qxg3+
36. Kh1 Qh3+ 37. Kg1 Qxe3+ 38. Kh1 Qh3+ 39. Kg1
{ (Black was winning in any case, but this move—most likely a product of time pressure—does a swan dive into the lava pit.) and White resigned without waiting for 39…Ng4, which forces a quick mate. In the end, White still rules the queenside, but his King is dead! }
